<docs>
	<doc for="PropertyCollection">
		<summary>
			<para>Represents a collection of properties that can be added to <see cref="System.Data.DataColumn"/>,
<see cref="System.Data.DataSet"/>,
   or <see cref="System.Data.DataTable"/>.</para>
		</summary>
		<remarks>
			<para>The <see cref="System.Data.PropertyCollection"/> can be accessed through the
<see langword="ExtendedProperties "/>property of the <see cref="System.Data.DataColumn"/>,
<see cref="System.Data.DataSet"/>,
   or <see cref="System.Data.DataTable"/> class.</para>
			<para>Add custom properties to the <see cref="System.Data.DataColumn"/>, <see cref="System.Data.DataSet"/>, or
   <see cref="System.Data.DataTable"/> objects through the <see cref="System.Data.PropertyCollection"/>. For example, you may want to store the time of the object's creation
   for later comparison to another object.</para>
		</remarks>
		<example>
			<para>The following example creates a timestamp value for a
   <see cref="System.Data.DataTable"/>
   and adds it to the <see cref="System.Data.PropertyCollection"/>.</para>
			<codelink SampleID="Classic WebData PropertyCollection Example" SnippetID="1"/>
		</example>
		<seealso cref="System.Data.DataColumn"/>
		<seealso cref="System.Data.DataSet"/>
		<seealso cref="System.Data.DataTable"/>
